---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { SITE, AUTHOR } from "../site.config";
---

<Base title="About">
  <h1>About</h1>

  <div class="article-body">
    <p>
      <strong>{SITE.title}</strong> is a <strong>FOSS-first AI publication</strong>
      by <strong>{AUTHOR.name}</strong> — {AUTHOR.description}
    </p>
    <p>
      We write deep technical guides, run reproducible benchmarks, demystify research
      papers, and publish based opinions. No affiliate links, no sponsored content,
      no hype.
    </p>

    <h2>Author</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>{AUTHOR.name}</strong> is a systems programmer and FOSS maximalist
      building AI infrastructure on bare metal — no cloud dependencies, no vendor lock-in.
      Active in the open-source LLM and self-hosted AI community.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/cleverlord">GitHub</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://twitter.com/substrate_pub">Twitter/X</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/cleverlord/substrate">Substrate (this project)</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How we work</h2>
    <p>
      Content is either <strong>hand-written in MDX</strong> or <strong>generated by
      our research pipeline</strong>:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>DeepSearch</strong> — SearXNG + Whoogle across 70+ engines</li>
      <li><strong>Crawl & Extract</strong> — Full-page markdown extraction</li>
      <li><strong>Embed & Retrieve</strong> — ChromaDB semantic search</li>
      <li><strong>Synthesize</strong> — DeepSeek reasoning over sources</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      Every generated post is <strong>human-reviewed</strong> before publication.
      All sources are cited. No AI slop, no SEO spam.
    </p>

    <h2>Stack</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> Astro + MDX + nginx — static, 0 client JS</li>
      <li><strong>Inference:</strong> DeepSeek via self-hosted gateway</li>
      <li><strong>Research:</strong> DeepSearchStack (SearXNG → crawl → embed → synthesize)</li>
      <li><strong>Infra:</strong> Docker Compose, bare metal, FOSS all the way down</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Principles</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>No JavaScript bloat.</strong> Reading pages are 100% HTML+CSS.</li>
      <li><strong>No tracking.</strong> No analytics, no cookies, no fingerprinting.</li>
      <li><strong>Full RSS.</strong> Every post, full content, no truncation.</li>
      <li><strong>Source everything.</strong> Citations, benchmarks, methodology — all public.</li>
      <li><strong>FOSS or die.</strong> Every component of the pipeline is open-source.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      <a href="/rss.xml">Subscribe via RSS</a>. No email, no notifications, just the feed.
    </p>
  </div>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Person",
    name: AUTHOR.name,
    url: AUTHOR.url,
    description: AUTHOR.description,
    sameAs: AUTHOR.sameAs,
    mainEntityOfPage: { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": `${SITE.url}/about/` },
  })} />
</Base>
